Place the carrots in a steamer and steam for 8–12 minutes, or until cooked through but still retaining a bite.Whisk together the oil, vinegar, honey, garlic, cinnamon, pinch of salt and lots of pepper in a large bowl. Add the carrots to the bowl and stir to combine. Set aside to cool.Mix together the yoghurt and crème fraîche in a bowl with pinch of salt. Add this to the carrots along with the fresh herbs. Stir through gently – you don’t want to overmix. Transfer to a serving bowl and serve immediately.